<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id748bc11f-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s90111"><num value="90111">§ 90111.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated to the foundation for carrying out the purposes of this chapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id748bc120-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s90111/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> $5,000,000 for fiscal year 2003; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id748bc121-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s90111/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> such sums as may be necessary for each succeeding fiscal year.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id748bc122-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/107/252/tVI/s601/a">Pub. L. 107–252, title VI, § 601(a)</ref>, <date date="2002-10-29">Oct. 29, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1721">116 Stat. 1721</ref>, § 152611; renumbered § 90111, <ref href="/us/pl/113/237/s3/c/6/B">Pub. L. 113–237, § 3(c)(6)(B)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-18">Dec. 18, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2840">128 Stat. 2840</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
